    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-12-06T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-12-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="904"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d904">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">818.6363/22</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Costa Rica</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hale</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-12-06">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 6, 1916</hi>.</date>
                    </dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 62</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The Department is in receipt of a despatch, dated
                    November 20, 1916, from the American Vice Consul at Port Limon, Costa Rica,
                    which states that the Constitutional Congress of the Republic of <pb facs="0974"
                        n="872" xml:id="pg_872"/> Costa Rica has granted to Doctor Leo J. Greulich,
                    of New York City, a concession for the privilege of exploring for and exploiting
                    petroleum and other hydro-carbonaceous substances in the Provinces of Limon,
                    Puntarenas, and Guanacaste.</p>
                <p>The Department desires that you investigate and report in full in regard to this
                    concession.</p>
                <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                <closer>For the Secretary of State:<lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Frank L. Polk</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
